Web3 has lost the plot‚Ä¶ thinking about what we have here versus the original whitepaper.

Peer-to-Peer Transactions

Bitcoin allows individuals to send money directly to each other without intermediaries.

Web3: Many Web3 platforms are becoming reliant on centralized exchanges (CEXs), where users must trust third parties to facilitate transactions rather than engaging in direct peer-to-peer transfers.

Decentralization

Bitcoin operates on a decentralized network where no single entity controls the system.

Web3: Some DeFi protocols and platforms are being built by centralized teams, with governance decisions made by a small group of developers or token holders, leading to a concentration of power.

Digital Signatures and Cryptographic Proof

Transactions are verified using cryptographic digital signatures, ensuring secure ownership transfers without revealing private information.

Web3: Web3 apps and services sometimes require extensive KYC (Know Your Customer) processes that compromise the privacy of users by collecting identifiable personal data, deviating from the original cryptographic proof-only model.

Incentives and Bitcoin Mining

Description: Miners are incentivized through block rewards and transaction fees to secure the network and validate transactions.

Web3: Many Web3 projects are overly dependent on unsustainable incentive mechanisms like high inflationary token rewards to attract participants, which can lead to devaluation of tokens and ‚Äúrug pulls‚Äù when incentives run dry.

Censorship Resistance

Bitcoin transactions cannot be censored or reversed by any central authority.

Web3: Some Web3 applications, especially those on centralized platforms or blockchains, have begun censoring transactions or freezing assets, undermining the censorship-resistant ethos of blockchain.

Irreversibility of Transactions

Description: Once a Bitcoin transaction is confirmed, it cannot be reversed or altered.

Web3: Certain platforms, especially centralized exchanges and custodial wallets, allow for transaction reversals or freeze funds upon request from regulators or other authorities.

Trustlessness

Bitcoin‚Äôs system doesn‚Äôt require trust in a central party; the protocol and cryptography handle security and verification.

Web3: Many Web3 projects introduce trust back into the system, requiring users to place trust in smart contract developers, centralized teams, or trusted multi-signature parties, reducing the trustless nature of decentralized technology.

1 song‚Ä¶ 1 BTC

When it happened earlier I didn‚Äôt quite realize right away what that really meant 

Despite knowing every inch of relentless work I put in for 3 years to get to this moment, it still didn‚Äôt feel real until‚Ä¶

I sat down at my childhood piano and, fighting the tears, I played the song. 

My song. My diary. My story.

But for the first time, it didn‚Äôt feel like I was singing the song. 
It felt like someone was singing it TO me. 
Someone who understood me and who knew to tell me I wasn‚Äôt crazy for being like this.

Someone who went through the same uphill battles who knew exactly what I needed to hear to keep going. 

And then I realized again that I was the one who wrote those lines. 
That I was giving me strength all along.
But that someone out there felt it too, enough to put such a value on it.
And so many others feel it as well, and show me every day.

The song brought me back to reality. 
The song told me the TRUTH.

My own song transcended me for a moment, comforted me, like it knew me before I consciously know myself. 

And it gave me strength and awareness that there‚Äôs a chance that now others who also felt misunderstood, defeated and lonely maybe now feel hopeful.

I think of all the artists (musicians in particular) out there who maybe experience this. 
And we forget that this is what our songs do to other people, until we‚Äôre so out of it ourselves that they do it to us.

Our own songs heal US first, before we even realize. And then they heal, unite, ignite hope in others too.

This is magic. Music is magic. Musi is God.

This is only the beginning, but right now I hold back the tears as I sing this little song about all the n0 0rdinary kinds that made it possible. 
Inspired by other art, powered by a defiant community 

To all that thought they‚Äôd be lonely forever 
They‚Äôd never get a chance 
That they may as well die 
But who kept going

You are not crazy. You are n0 0rdinary kind.

And this song is for you.

cleaned_data.original_text:
I just mapped out well-known Bitcoin nodes using data from Bitnodes, plotting their locations on a world map with a custom-built control (something I've done for Cardano many times before). This visualization really highlights the decentralization of Bitcoin. Even more interesting is that approximately 12,389 nodes, around +62.8%, aren't shown here due to location data not being available.  It really does show how decentralized and amazing Bitcoin truly is. 

In the near future, Bitcoin will gain the ability to leverage Cardano's smart contract capabilities. This means that smart contracts can execute on the Bitcoin mainnet, with Cardano acting as a smart contract platform for the largest asset base in the world. With this in mind, I plan to simulate interactions between the Bitcoin blockchain and Cardano, which will be a challenging task but I really want to try and show a visual interaction here because it is truly historic. 

I hope this visualization provides value, as I haven't come across a representation of Bitcoin nodes quite like this before. For those interested, here‚Äôs a live link to explore the interactive map: Live Link (Available for probably ~10 minutes only). Feel free to screenshot and share before the link expires! üòä

https://t.co/cs1UqgTstt

Art vs. Money

Bitcoin Maxis argue that money‚Äôs utility surpasses art‚Äôs value. But does history agree?

Few remember the 15th-century Florentine florin, once a dominant currency. Yet when Da Vinci‚Äôs Salvator Mundi sold for $450M, the world was captivated.

Value isn‚Äôt just about utility or profit‚Äîit‚Äôs about what moves us and endures. Bitcoin might be the future of finance, but art, stories, and soul-stirring moments are remembered for centuries.

That $450M Da Vinci? Not just a painting ‚Äî it‚Äôs human history, emotion, culture. For me, Bitcoin inscriptions hold similar timeless potential.

Bitcoin may revolutionize finance, but can it capture our hearts like art? Sound money protects against inflation, but art captures eternity, speaks to future generations, and inspires humanity to new heights.

The absurd grounds for the persecution and the even more outrageous extradition request are reminiscent of other political trials undertaken by the American empire against its critics, such as @Cobratate, @officialmcafee, @RealRossU, @Snowden, @durov, @KimDotcom and @JulianAssange_. 

It is time for European nations to start pushing back and resist such American legal terror. My motion will be put to a vote later tonight.
